3.2 VULNERABILITY OVERVIEW
 3.2.1    OUT-OF-BOUNDS READ CWE-125
The affected application is vulnerable to out-of-bounds read past the end of an allocated buffer when parsing X_T files. An attacker could leverage this vulnerability to leak information in the context of the current process.
CVE-2022-39137 has been assigned to this vulnerability. A CVSS v3 base score of 3.3 has been calculated; the CVSS vector string is (AV:L/AC:L/PR:N/UI:R/S:U/C:L/I:N/A:N).
